const object and const methods

When you have constant objects only constant methods can be calLed on it. 
const methods are declared with the 'const' keyword at the end of their signature.

example:

int	main()
{
	const A a;		//const object of class A
	a.method();	//method is a const method, so you can call 'a' on it.
}

class A {
public:
    void method() const 		//
   {
	//some code	
  }
};
